WEBVTT

00:07.000 --> 00:09.000
[pulsing music playing]

00:27.833 --> 00:29.916
♪ ♪

00:49.083 --> 00:51.582
[Kara] <i>For those who voyage
among the stars,</i>

00:51.583 --> 00:54.541
<i>time is the most precious resource.</i>

00:57.083 --> 00:59.749
<i>In starships traveling near light speed,</i>

00:59.750 --> 01:03.082
<i>time slows to a crawl.</i>

01:03.083 --> 01:07.083
<i>Days for a traveler could be years
for their loved ones back home.</i>

01:10.000 --> 01:12.415
<i>Lidon is a frontier planet,</i>

01:12.416 --> 01:14.665
<i>a new world that had always been too small</i>

01:14.666 --> 01:16.791
<i>to hold Mari Hanson.</i>

01:18.625 --> 01:20.250
[beeping]

01:22.000 --> 01:24.332
<i>Life was difficult here,</i>

01:24.333 --> 01:28.332
<i>especially for this first generation
off the arcship from Earth.</i>

01:28.333 --> 01:31.874
<i>Mari's mother died
in a harsh winter soon after landfall,</i>

01:31.875 --> 01:35.207
<i>and her father, Nik,
raised her the best he could.</i>

01:35.208 --> 01:37.707
Dad, you hear about Calen?

01:37.708 --> 01:39.999
He got a spot on an off-world expedition.

01:40.000 --> 01:41.499
He's probably gonna be gone for decades.

01:41.500 --> 01:44.915
I heard. Hand me that spanner.

01:44.916 --> 01:47.415
Calen was saying
that there's still an opening,

01:47.416 --> 01:49.832
and I was thinking maybe
I could be the one to take it--

01:49.833 --> 01:52.582
Mari, we've been over this.

01:52.583 --> 01:54.582
You're too young and it's too dangerous.

01:54.583 --> 01:57.457
But Dad, I'm only a few months short.

01:57.458 --> 01:59.040
Nobody's gonna check my registry, and--

01:59.041 --> 02:02.040
[Rafael] Spoken like a true traveler.

02:02.041 --> 02:05.332
Rules are for those who lack imagination.

02:05.333 --> 02:07.874
Rafe Sabatine. You must be...

02:07.875 --> 02:09.916
On her way home.

02:10.041 --> 02:12.624
It'll take three days
to fix the port thruster,

02:12.625 --> 02:14.707
but the valve'll hold
till you get to Scotia.

02:14.708 --> 02:17.540
Scotia? That's your home port?

02:17.541 --> 02:19.415
[scoffs] Gods, no.

02:19.416 --> 02:21.874
Scotia's a celestial graveyard,

02:21.875 --> 02:25.749
but I hear there's still artifacts
buried in those ruins.

02:25.750 --> 02:28.457
Hmm. Maybe you can find an artifact

02:28.458 --> 02:30.957
that would make Lidon less of a...

02:30.958 --> 02:34.166
- Frozen hellscape? [laughs]
- [laughs]

02:43.416 --> 02:45.541
[gentle music playing]

02:47.166 --> 02:49.957
Finally done with Sabatine's ship.

02:49.958 --> 02:52.665
Held together with tape and chewing gum,
but she'll fly.

02:52.666 --> 02:54.665
Nope, she won't.

02:54.666 --> 02:57.582
Got a message from Melayu
asking us to impound the ship.

02:57.583 --> 03:00.165
His father's refusing the bill.

03:00.166 --> 03:02.790
Seems the kid borrowed it
without permission.

03:02.791 --> 03:06.290
Aw, every traveler's a thief,
but stealing from your own family?

03:06.291 --> 03:08.707
Yeah, that boy's all kinds of trouble.

03:08.708 --> 03:11.916
I can see why Mari's so smitten.

03:13.583 --> 03:14.957
Come on, Nik.

03:14.958 --> 03:16.915
Even you can't be that dense.

03:16.916 --> 03:18.541
[rumbling]

03:21.791 --> 03:23.875
That sneaky son of a bitch.

03:46.541 --> 03:48.499
She's just a kid.

03:48.500 --> 03:52.374
[Kara] <i>Nik wasn't a wealthy man,
but his daughter was everything.</i>

03:52.375 --> 03:54.583
<i>He had to get her back.</i>

03:55.666 --> 03:58.540
<i>And so, Thadie Voss loaned Nik the money</i>

03:58.541 --> 04:02.582
<i>to buy himself into the crew
of the</i> Southern Cross.

04:02.583 --> 04:05.582
<i>The cargo hauler made slow crossings,</i>

04:05.583 --> 04:08.040
<i>but one port of call was Scotia,</i>

04:08.041 --> 04:11.750
<i>the same world his daughter was bound for.</i>

04:16.875 --> 04:22.165
<i>Traveling at near light speed,
one year passed for Nik</i>

04:22.166 --> 04:26.207
<i>while eight years passed
for Mari on Scotia.</i>

04:26.208 --> 04:29.249
<i>Once a thriving Celestial world,</i>

04:29.250 --> 04:32.332
<i>now a radioactive hellscape.</i>

04:32.333 --> 04:35.124
<i>Some expeditions to her harsh surface</i>

04:35.125 --> 04:37.540
<i>found priceless artifacts.</i>

04:37.541 --> 04:40.207
<i>Most found death.</i>

04:40.208 --> 04:42.915
<i>But Nik refused to give up hope.</i>

04:42.916 --> 04:46.790
<i>Rafe and Mari had joined
a poorly outfitted expedition,</i>

04:46.791 --> 04:48.457
<i>a gamble that nearly killed them both.</i>

04:48.458 --> 04:50.165
<i>But it was Mari who rescued Rafe</i>

04:50.166 --> 04:52.874
<i>from the remnants guarding the ruins.</i>

04:52.875 --> 04:56.249
<i>Nik had spent only months
in sliptime on the cargo hauler,</i>

04:56.250 --> 04:58.082
<i>but in actual time,</i>

04:58.083 --> 05:02.040
<i>Mari and Rafe had suffered
long, hard years on Scotia.</i>

05:02.041 --> 05:04.499
<i>Nik followed them to Melayu,</i>

05:04.500 --> 05:07.832
<i>home world of the Sabatine family.</i>

05:07.833 --> 05:09.916
[intriguing music playing]

05:15.125 --> 05:17.040
[Luca] <i>I am sorry, Nik.</i>

05:17.041 --> 05:20.040
You've come a long way for bad news.

05:20.041 --> 05:24.415
Rafe and Mari left 12 years ago
for Hevelius.

05:24.416 --> 05:28.707
They were after a map
of lost Détenir worlds.

05:28.708 --> 05:30.625
But something went wrong.

05:34.583 --> 05:35.874
[Mari over video] <i>Rafe!</i>

05:35.875 --> 05:37.958
<i>Get to the ship.</i>

05:39.291 --> 05:41.082
[Luca] We know they lifted off,

05:41.083 --> 05:45.290
but we lost contact
when the ship left the system.

05:45.291 --> 05:48.915
The Celestials will follow them,

05:48.916 --> 05:51.540
hunt them.

05:51.541 --> 05:53.166
I'd give anything to help, but...

05:54.791 --> 05:57.458
[growls]

05:59.583 --> 06:01.208
A ship.

06:02.833 --> 06:05.208
Give me a ship.

06:14.041 --> 06:15.999
[Kara] <i>Nik knew Mari and Rafe
would be executed</i>

06:16.000 --> 06:18.915
<i>for their theft if they were found.</i>

06:18.916 --> 06:22.749
<i>In desperation,
Nik surrendered himself to the Celestials,</i>

06:22.750 --> 06:26.749
<i>becoming a member
of their indentured human crew.</i>

06:26.750 --> 06:28.665
<i>He hoped that if they found Mari,</i>

06:28.666 --> 06:30.875
<i>he could find some way...</i>

06:32.291 --> 06:34.125
<i>...to save her.</i>

06:35.125 --> 06:37.125
[eerie music playing]

06:57.583 --> 06:59.583
[intense music playing]

07:09.541 --> 07:11.541
[alarm beeping]

07:14.416 --> 07:16.707
Rafe. Shut those fucking hatches.

07:16.708 --> 07:18.957
<i>Just a few more, Mari!</i>

07:18.958 --> 07:21.040
<i>Can't let this all be for nothing.
[grunts]</i>

07:21.041 --> 07:23.374
[man] <i>Celestials!
We need to get out of here!</i>

07:23.375 --> 07:24.832
- [Rafe] <i>There's too many!
- [man] They've got us surrounded!</i>

07:24.833 --> 07:27.624
<i>[woman] Evac now. I repeat, evac now.</i>

07:27.625 --> 07:29.874
Shit! They're gonna rip us apart!

07:29.875 --> 07:31.916
Strap in! I'm lifting!

07:35.875 --> 07:37.875
[alarm blaring]

07:47.291 --> 07:49.290
[man] <i>Head for the gate!
They can't be far behind us.</i>

07:49.291 --> 07:51.665
[man 2] <i>We've got incoming! [exclaims]</i>

07:51.666 --> 07:53.582
<i>Traveler down! Repeat, traveler down!</i>

07:53.583 --> 07:57.166
[woman] <i>Celestial ships are ahead.
They've cut us off from the gate.</i>

08:02.416 --> 08:04.166
Sending in the clear for <i>La Castella.</i>

08:05.250 --> 08:06.540
<i>Mari, if you can hear me,</i>

08:06.541 --> 08:08.665
<i>do exactly as I say.</i>

08:08.666 --> 08:11.624
- That voice.
<i>- Make your run for the gate</i>

08:11.625 --> 08:13.749
<i>as close to the warship as possible.</i>

08:13.750 --> 08:16.582
[man] <i>Mari, pull up. Mari. Mari! Pull up!</i>

08:16.583 --> 08:20.083
[woman] <i>We need to pull back!</i>
[man] <i>They're locked on. I can't evade!</i>

08:21.666 --> 08:23.249
Dad!

08:23.250 --> 08:24.415
<i>Where are you?</i>

08:24.416 --> 08:27.415
Mari, I'm in a shuttle
on a Celestial ship,

08:27.416 --> 08:29.457
but I'm going to detonate their reactor

08:29.458 --> 08:30.666
<i>in three...</i>

08:32.916 --> 08:34.915
<i>...two...</i>

08:34.916 --> 08:36.666
[grunts]

08:47.083 --> 08:49.041
[exciting music playing]

08:52.875 --> 08:54.707
<i>Mari, fighters on your tail.</i>

08:54.708 --> 08:56.166
I see 'em!

09:06.125 --> 09:08.250
I can't lose 'em!

09:11.125 --> 09:12.457
[Nik] <i>Hold on!</i>

09:12.458 --> 09:14.375
I'm coming, Mari!

09:21.708 --> 09:23.707
[Mari] Rafe.

09:23.708 --> 09:25.750
I'm sorry.

09:31.333 --> 09:33.624
[Nik] <i>Mari.</i>

09:33.625 --> 09:35.166
[distant] Mari!

09:53.166 --> 09:55.166
[gentle music playing]

10:16.625 --> 10:19.040
[Kara] <i>Through some miracle,</i>

10:19.041 --> 10:21.208
<i>Mari survived.</i>

10:27.541 --> 10:29.958
<i>But Mari's injuries were too severe.</i>

10:31.833 --> 10:35.582
We found thousand-year-old technology

10:35.583 --> 10:37.791
that was more advanced than ours.

10:39.541 --> 10:43.040
Celestials have built empires
across the entire cluster.

10:43.041 --> 10:44.207
Most...

10:44.208 --> 10:46.291
[strained inhale, groans]

10:47.333 --> 10:49.415
...have yet to be discovered.

10:49.416 --> 10:52.250
[Kara] <i>Nik did his best to extend
the time they had together.</i>

10:53.250 --> 10:54.833
<i>But in the end...</i>

10:56.250 --> 10:57.916
<i>...he had to let her go.</i>

10:58.916 --> 11:00.957
<i>He took solace that she'd lived the life</i>

11:00.958 --> 11:03.041
<i>of adventure and wonder.</i>

11:04.041 --> 11:06.875
<i>The life of a traveler.</i>

11:11.625 --> 11:12.749
That's right.

11:12.750 --> 11:15.415
I'm gonna need those engines
back online by 0800.

11:15.416 --> 11:16.915
[man] <i>Copy that.</i>

11:16.916 --> 11:19.000
<i>Engines online by 0800.</i>

11:25.541 --> 11:27.165
Kara Voss?

11:27.166 --> 11:28.499
Yeah. That's right.

11:28.500 --> 11:30.500
I'm a little busy.

11:31.500 --> 11:34.500
Your grandmother Thady and I
were good friends.

11:35.583 --> 11:37.707
I owed her a debt.

11:37.708 --> 11:39.583
With her gone...

11:40.666 --> 11:43.041
...I reckon this belongs to you.

11:45.166 --> 11:47.708
A little something
to help warm this place up.

11:49.416 --> 11:51.000
Hold on.

11:52.083 --> 11:54.790
This is worth more than every ship here.

11:54.791 --> 11:56.707
And Port Bering besides.

11:56.708 --> 12:00.000
Figured I owed a bit of interest.

12:03.500 --> 12:05.000
[door closes]

12:06.041 --> 12:08.041
[optimistic music playing]

12:37.333 --> 12:39.625
[exciting music playing]

13:07.666 --> 13:09.958
♪ ♪

13:37.583 --> 13:39.833
♪ ♪

14:02.750 --> 14:05.000
♪ ♪
